                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17730707-11-off64 t17730707-11-crimeloc67"></join>; I missed it there; he seemed to be sweating; then he said he had been carrying a heavy bundle; he shewed us where he had left the bundle; it turned out to be a sack with two stitches of bacon, and then I secured him.</p>
               <p>The waggoner deposed that the prisoner rode in his waggon to Hammersmith; that there he got out and had nothing with him then; that he supposed he threw it out of the tale of the waggon; and so when he got out he carried it off; he rode in the waggon and sat on the sack.</p>
